The paper deals with the complexity of Maximum Clique in intersection graphs of convex objects in the plane, specifically focusing on disk-like graphs. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and hardness proofs, which are relevant to approximation algorithms (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
